MAG Dereplication and Microdiversity Profiling Workflow
This workflow describes the procedures used for MAG dereplication, read mapping, genome indexing, and microdiversity profiling using dRep, bowtie2, prodigal, and inStrain.
1. Directory structure
Before running the workflow, prepare the following directories:
temp/        # Clean data folder
mags/        # MAG files
result/      # Output folder
Place the metadata.txt file in the result/ directory.
The expected metadata file is:
result/metadata.txt

2. Dereplicate MAGs using dRep
#Activate the conda environment
conda activate genome
#Run dRep dereplication
dRep dereplicate dRep -g mags/*.fna -p 60 -pa 0.9 -sa 0.95 -nc 0.3 -cm larger -comp 90 -con 5 1> log.deredundancy_log

3. Merge dereplicated MAGs into one FASTA file
cat dRep/dereplicated_genomes/*.fna > allGenomes_v1.fasta

4. Build the Bowtie2 index for MAGs
#Create a new folder named bt2 before building the index.
bowtie2-build allGenomes_v1.fasta bt2/allGenomes_v1.fasta

5. Quality control for raw sequencing data
#If the input files are raw data, perform quality control first.
#If the input files are already clean data, skip this step.
tail -n+2 result/metadata.txt|cut -f1|rush -j 2 \
      "fastp -i seq/{1}_R1.fq.gz -o temp/{1}_1.fastq -I seq/{1}_r2.fq.gz -O temp/{1}_2.fastq"

6. Generate SAM files by mapping clean reads to MAGs
tail -n+2 result/metadata.txt|cut -f1|rush -j 1 \
      "bowtie2 -p 80 -x bt2/allGenomes_v1.fasta -1 temp/{1}.clean.1.fq -2 temp/{1}.clean.2.fq > allGenomes_v1.fasta-vs-{1}.sam"

7. Predict gene sequences from MAGs
#Activate the conda environment
conda activate metagenome
#Run Prodigal
prodigal -i allGenomes_v1.fasta -d allGenomes_v1.fasta.genes.fna

8. Generate the .stb file for inStrain
#This step is performed in R on a local computer using the script stb.R.
#Check the format of the .stb file:
head allGenomes_v1.fasta.maxbin2.stb
Procedure:
(1)	Put the dereplicated MAG files in the same folder as the stb.R script.
(2)	Copy and paste the MAG file names into mag1.txt.
(3)	Run stb.R.
(4)	Copy the content of result_df.csv into allGenomes_v1.fasta.maxbin2.stb on the server.

9. Calculate microdiversity using inStrain
#Activate the conda environment
conda activate instrain2
#Run inStrain profile for each sample
tail -n+2 result/metadata.txt|cut -f1|rush -j 1 \
      "inStrain profile allGenomes_v1.fasta-vs-{1}.sam allGenomes_v1.fasta -o result/allGenomes_v1.fasta-vs-{1}.IS -p 60 -g allGenomes_v1.fasta.genes.fna -s allGenomes_v1.fasta.maxbin2.stb"

Output files
The main output files include:
dRep/                                      # dRep dereplication results
allGenomes_v1.fasta                        # Merged dereplicated MAGs
bt2/                                       # Bowtie2 index files
allGenomes_v1.fasta-vs-{sample}.sam        # Read-mapping SAM files
allGenomes_v1.fasta.genes.fna              # Predicted gene sequences
allGenomes_v1.fasta.maxbin2.stb            # Scaffold-to-bin file
result/allGenomes_v1.fasta-vs-{sample}.IS  # inStrain output directory for each sample
